# âœ… Linux Privilege Escalation (Advanced Techniques) 

### ğŸ“‚ PATH Abuse (Writable Directory Hijack)

- [ ] `echo $PATH` â€” Look for any custom or suspicious paths (`/home/user/bin`, etc.)
- [ ] `ls -la /path/` â€” Check if any directory inside PATH is **writable**.
- [ ] If writable: Craft a malicious binary (like `cat`, `cp`, or custom) and wait for cron/script execution.

âœ… _Pro Tip_: Abuse misconfigured scripts that run with elevated privileges but call unquoted binaries!

