### ğŸ Python Library Hijacking

- [ ]  Look for scripts run with `sudo`, `cron`, or services â†’ `pspy` / manual cron checks.
- [ ] Check imports: `grep "import" script.py`
- [ ] If libraries like `os`, `sys`, etc. are imported:
- [ ] Check if any local folder is writable.
- [ ] Inject malicious module (same name) to hijack execution.

âœ… _Pro Tip_: Drop malicious `os.py` or `requests.py` if script loads modules insecurely!

